<br>
Obviously, China is one huge motherfuhka of a country too.  No one is fuhking with them.  Plus, they are actually coming a long way in human rights.  Things were worse decades ago. Change doesnt happen overnight. <br>
<br>
Africa is a hotbed of tribal conflict.  UN and many nations have tried to help there but it just goes on again.  Its not even with real military weapons for the most part.  Tribal war has been a reality in Africa since before Ceasar found the middle of march a perplexing date. <br>
<br>
How do you change thousands of years of tribal warfare?  <br>
<br>
So, a couple simple questions:<br>
1) How would have leaving Saddam, a person who has killed over 2 million people in Iraq, improved the prospects for peace in the middle east and saved lives? <br>
<br>
2) How do you fix the problems of Africa peacefully?  With military?  <br>
<br>
3) How do you propose we get the Chinese out of Tibet without causing a war you could not even imagine the worst consequences of? <br>
<br>
Its fine to say why not this and why not that.  But, at least have a way to do it first.  There was a way and a basis for going into Iraq, provided to us by Saddams invasion of Kuwait and agreed cease fire with us.  Syria is not on the table for attack. Stop buying the liberal press trying to incite stuff against the administration. Even Rumsfeld, when talking about Syria's problems, said war is not in the list of options to resolve it (and we know he says it like it is. He still leaves military options open against North Korea). <br>
<br>
Now, on the nuclear ban in the middle east.  Great, we have Israel with nuclear weapons they wont use but are a deterent against the chemical weapons that we know many of the other countries are hiding around there.  We forcefully disarm Israels nukes and guess what? That little island in a sea of Islam is suddenly swamped and you might as well say genocide.  Im not saying the Israelies are without fault, but you dont just take away the one thing that keeps that tidal wave from sinking in on them, you do what is happening now and pressure them to reach a peaceful agreement with Palestine (thus diffusing the situation). <br>
